	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>10 Jany 5690</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName>Mr M Joseph</persName> has paid<lb/> me three dollars for a years subscription<lb/> to the Occident which I have requested<lb/> <persName>Miss Sarah J.</persName> to pay you&#44; if on funds.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mrs S. Benjamin</persName> has<lb/> written to inquire about the price<lb/> of a Bible bound in the manner<lb/> and for the purpose <persName>Sarah J.</persName> will explain<lb/>&#8212;or has explained&#8212;to you.  I only<lb/> refer to it to request you to intimate<lb/> to <persName>Mr S. B.</persName> that he would oblige<lb/> by paying to me the amount he<lb/> owes you&#8212;this <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I enclose a review&#8212;not<lb/> <hi rend="underline">laudatory</hi> or <hi rend="underline">elaborate</hi> enough of<lb/> one of the best books I have ever</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>seen on the subject of the <add>&#63;</add><lb/>  I have paid some little attention to<lb/> this subject&#44; but am better pleased<lb/> with <persName>Dr. D&#39;s</persName> book than with many<lb/> more pretentious ones.  Any one<lb/> who has carefully read <persName>Hugh<lb/> Millers</persName> Lestim<add>&#63;</add> any of the Books<lb/> can well understand why he<lb/> shot himself.  If I had been<lb/> an agent for an Insurance Office<lb/> where he had published and I<lb/> had read&#44; I would not&#44; if he<lb/> had applied to me have taken the risk.<lb/>  And he has been immo<add>&#63;</add><lb/> I think made too much of it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr. D.</persName> has a claim on<lb/> Jews for a little <add>Hebrew</add>.  We<lb/> respect Hebrew learning and</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>the Hebrew language.  True it is<lb/> that the Hebrew chair at McGill<lb/> College was filled by <add>&#63;</add> years before<lb/> <persName>Dr. D.</persName> came to this country&#44; and<lb/> I have not to thank him either for my<lb/> appointment&#44; or for favoring the<lb/> chair.  Yet I do thank him that he<lb/> has invariably in his published<lb/> writings shown how important is<lb/> the study of Hebrew to all.  But <persName>Dr<lb/> D.</persName> has this special claim on us<lb/> just now.  He is a learned naturalist<lb/>&#8212;a man of depth&#44; and he is out<lb/> on <hi rend="underline">our</hi> side&#44; and not on the<lb/> side of flippant shallow German<lb/> rationalists&#8212;who have imprudence<lb/> enough to spare.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I would recommend<lb/> <persName><sic>Dr. D.s</sic></persName> book to brother <persName>Wise</persName>&#8212;he<lb/> seems to be in agony just now on</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>the subject&#44; and will no doubt<lb/> soon come out with a pragmatical<lb/> Introductory on the cosma<add>&#63;</add><lb/> taking off his hat to <persName>Adam</persName><lb/> &#38; <persName>Eve</persName>&#44; for re<add>&#63;</add> with <persName>Abraham</persName><lb/> &#38; not them&#8212;but he will have<lb/> to turn the earth inside out to<lb/> get at the truth.  The articles<lb/> in the Israelite on the historys<add>&#63;</add> of<lb/> geology are printed as far as I<lb/> have noticed without a <add>&#63;</add><lb/> <add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If you print my notice<lb/> of <persName>Dr D&#39;s</persName> book&#44; please do so at once<lb/> and address an additional copy<lb/> to <persName>Dr D</persName>&#8212;to my care&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Remain Yrs truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
				<p>Why do I never<lb/> hear from you<lb/> Will you oblige me by mailing the enclosed<lb/> for <persName>Andrew Cohen</persName>.  I do not know his right address</p>
		</body>
